                                                <p><name type="person"><hi rend="initialcap">W</hi>AGNER, <hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>HARLES</name>, Private, <name type="organization">Co. L, 1st New York
                                                                Cavalry</name>, aged 25 years.  Pistol ball fracture of
                                                  temporal.  <name type="place" key="#Washington">Washington</name>, <date type="operation" when="1865-06-26"><date type="admit" when="1865-06-26">June 26th, 1865</date></date>.  <name type="hospital" key="171">Armory Square Hospital</name>.  Removal of fragments by <name type="person" key="123">Surgeon D. W. Bliss</name>, <name type="organization" key="132">U. S. V.</name>, and ligation of posterior
                                                                auricular.  Transferred to <name type="hospital" key="173">Harewood Hospital</name> <date type="transfer" when="1865-08-15">August
                                                                  15th</date>; discharged <date type="servicedischarge" when="1865-10-12">October 12th, 1865</date>.  <name type="organization" key="xxx">Pension Office</name> reports, <date type="pension" when="1868-07-10">July 10th, 1868</date>, disability total.  <name type="person">Examiner P. S. Treadwell</name>, <date type="pension" when="1869-12-13">December 13th, 1869</date>, states that insanity is said to have ensued.</p>                                       
